The paper deals with the problem of global registration of heterogeneous ground and aerial mapping data, which is a common problem in robotics. The paper evaluates different approaches for feature extraction, descriptors, and transformation estimation for this task. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper extensively uses point-cloud data from vision sensors, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques for feature extraction and transformation estimation, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of disaster response, which suggests that it may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
